<Content>Good excercise facility, a little tired looking My stay at this hotel was off to a good start when I was upgraded to a very large suite named for a famous Texas figure. I had a hallway, bar, living room and bedroom. Extremely spacious! I thought while it was nice, it had some deferred maintenance, such as the rose colored carpet faded in spots and needed to be replaced. The bathroom, while large and nice, needed to be updated because it screamed 1980 to me.On the weekday, there was a free continetal breakfast, but the room was in horrible condition, not at all nice.I ate in the almost empty dining room which aslo needed to be updated, because it looked very 1975 to me. The food was just OK.The ground are lovely and a very large campus. The buildings looked like they needed to be repainted about 3 years ago. The excercise facility was nice, but also a little old looking. I belong to The Houstonian in Houston, ( the first Prez Bush is a member) and it is the workout facility at Cooper was not nearly as nice as The Houstonian.Tip: If you did not bring your laptop, they have a free computer with internet access for guests. 
