<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Awesome Escape What a wonderful surprise! This hotel was located on the most beautiful campus I have ever seen. It is like you are at a weekend retreat right in the heart of Dallas. I had no idea you could stay here until a friend of mine suggested it, and it couldn't have been better. The staff is so nice and courteous, and because of the small size, you get personal attention. It feels a little like camp for grownups becuase you have access to the awesome fitness center and the 2 heated pools. There is a track that weaves throughout the campus for walking or jogging, and the scenery is gorgeous. There are ponds, flowers, tress, and even ducks and squirrels. You can park right up next to the building, and parking is free. They have a wonderful spa that I took full advantage of, and also 2 restaurants. One is more formal dining, and the other is sort of like a deli with sandwiches and smoothies. The food there is so good, and most of it is good for you. I was so impressed with how clean my room was when I got back to it...you could literally eat off the floor! And, they have free turndown service at night...it really make you feel important. Everyone there was so nice and the place was so awesome that I will definately be staying there for all of my Dallas visits. 
